STATE OF FLORIDA, ex rel. S. M. MERCER, v. J. E. ALBRITTON, Sheriff of DeSoto County, Florida. 11 So. (2nd) 305

June Term, 1942

January 11, 1943 Division B W. W. Whitehurst, for appellant. J. Tom Watson, Attorney General, and Woodrow M. Melvin, Assistant Attorney General, for appellee. PER CURIAM:

No error having been made clearly to appear the order of the circuit judge denying the petitioner’s application for writ of habeas corpus is—

Affirmed.

BROWN, C. J., TERRELL, CHAPMAN and THOMAS, JJ., concur.
